summary: An ordinance relating to and authorizing the leasing of Incinerator No. 2, on the north side of Lake Union, and the property upon which the same is located, comprising portions of Blocks six (6) and nine (9), Burke's First Addition, Supplemental Plat of Block three (3) of Burke's Addition to the City of Seattle; vacated North 29th Street and vacated Northlake Avenue, and Block forty-four (44) of the Lake Union Shore Lands; providing for the execution of a contract of lease in respect thereto, and repealing Ordinance No. 42385, passed June 20, 1921, and approved June 22, 1921.
